1.00	Dr._Heckyll_and_Mr._Jive	Dr. Heckyll and Mr. Jive	"Dr. Heckyll and Mr. Jive" is a song by the Australian group Men at Work. The song was written by Men at Work singer/guitarist Colin Hay, and the recording was produced by Peter McIan. It was released in November 1983 as the third single from their album Cargo, after "Overkill" and "It's a Mistake". "Dr. Heckyll and Mr. Jive" was the band's last hit single in the US Top 40, peaking at #28 on the Billboard Hot 100 in November 1983. The song is about a mad scientist named Dr. Heckyll who creates a potion that turns him into a handsome, talkative man. The lyric is a parody of The Strange Case of Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde.	
